The paper deals with the problem of image retrieval based on visual queries, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The proposed method involves the use of Voronoi-based spatial partitioning, which is a technique commonly used in computational geometry (cs.CG) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves the use of deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which is a popular topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multimedia (cs.MM). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.CV and cs.IR, followed by cs.MM, cs.LG, and cs.AI.
